HEADWORD: Annulosa
<hw>An"nu*lo"sa</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of the Invertebrata,
nearly equivalent to the Articulata. It includes the Arthoropoda and
Anarthropoda. By some Zoologists it is applied to the former
only.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

